{"lemma":"طَهُورِ","slug":"طَهُورِ","root":"ط.ه.ر","root_slug":"ط-ه-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ط-ه-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"طَهُور","root":"طهر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27218"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B7%D9%8E%D9%87%D9%8F%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27218","headword_ar":"طَهُورٌ","root":"Thr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. of 1; as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuhuwrN","text_ar":"طُهُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and inf. n. [or rather quasi-inf. n.] of 5. (Sb, Mgh, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"[such as water]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which one cleanses"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purifies:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, Mgh, Msb, K:) a word similar to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faTuwrN","text_ar":"فَطُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHuwrN","text_ar":"سَحُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waquwdN","text_ar":"وَقُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) and the author of the “ Matáli' el-Anwár ” mentions"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuhuwrN","text_ar":"طُهُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also in this sense; but this is strange and anomalous: (En-Nawawee:) the former occurs in the Kur xxv. 50: (S:) or it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water with which the ablution termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wuDuwo'","text_ar":"وُضُوْء"},{"kind":"text","text":"is performed: (A, IAth:) or it has the signification next following. (K.) It is said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~awobapu TahuwrN","text_ar":"التَّوْبَةُ طَهُورٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lilomu*onibi","text_ar":"لِلْمُذْنِبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Repentance is a means of purifying the sinner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"criminal"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) Lth says that it is that which is [accompanied] by the execution of the prescribed punishment, such as stoning &c. (TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maToharapN","text_ar":"مَطْهَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A2-  It is also an epithet, (Mgh, TA,) and signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Clean and cleansing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pure and purifying:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, T, Mgh, Msb:) whatever God has created descending from the sky, or welling forth from the earth as a spring or river or sea, in which a human being does nothing but drawing water, and of which the colour is not changed by anything mixing with it, nor the taste thereby, is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tahuwr","text_ar":"طَهُور"},{"kind":"text","text":": and what is otherwise, as the water of roses and of the leaves of trees, and what flows from the grape-vine, though it be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAhir","text_ar":"طَاهِر"},{"kind":"text","text":", is not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tahuwr","text_ar":"طَهُور"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Esh-Sháfi'ee:) the former removes impurities: the latter, if not at the same time"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tahuwr","text_ar":"طَهُور"},{"kind":"text","text":", does not: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very clean"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pure:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb:) the explanation by Th, if meant to show that the word signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the utmost cleanness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pureness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"is correct and good: otherwise, it is not so; for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEuwlN","text_ar":"فَعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is not formed from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tafoEiylN","text_ar":"تَفْعِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh, O:) it is also explained as signifying, simply,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cleansing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"purifying:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(B, TA:) also as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAhirN","text_ar":"طَاهِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyquhun~a TahuwrN","text_ar":"رِيقُهُنَّ طَهُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their saliva is pure"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: but here it is either an intensive epithet or used for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAhirN","text_ar":"طَاهِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for the sake of the measure. (Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","T","S","Mgh","Msb","K","A","IAth","Th","O","B"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}